CHANGELOG.md:127:- Added depth-2 syncopation-features end-to-end test coverage (frac-0117): `tests/test_syncopation_features.py` now declares `depth: 2` in its module docstring and includes `SyncopationFeaturesEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing syncopation + polyrhythmic-cross surface across `my-claw/tools/senseweave/groove_engine.py` and `my-claw/tools/senseweave/music_tracker.py` through one realistic groove lifecycle: `_GROOVE_PROFILES["syncopated"]` and `_GROOVE_PROFILES["polyrhythmic_cross"]` resolve to registered profiles with non-zero `syncopation_intensity` and non-empty `lane_phase_offsets` (with `polyrhythm == (3, 4)` for the cross profile), `_parse_lane_phase_offsets("0,1,2,3,1")` agrees with the directly supplied `(0, 1, 2, 3, 1)` tuple, `syncopate_phrase(...)` at `intensity=1.0` deterministically inserts leading rests into a four-note melody phrase while preserving total duration and stamping `metadata["syncopated"] == "true"`, the same call at `intensity=0.6` produces at least as many melody rests as bass rests under the same RNG seed, `_quantize_phrase_to_lane(... phase_offset_rows=2)` shifts the melody first step row to row 2 while exempting the bass first step row at row 0, and a primitive diagnostic of profiles, parsed offsets, rest counts, durations, first-step rows, and `DEFAULT_LANE_PHASE_OFFSETS` round-trips through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_syncopation_features_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2, requires the named end-to-end class/method, and requires the machine-readable `depth: 2` marker. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the syncopation + polyrhythmic-cross surface already produced meaningful one-path output; startup identity anchors remain green (`11 passed`) and the full validation gate (`4673 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remains clean, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:129:- Tightened sw_sampler end-to-end JSON diagnostic coverage (frac-0116c): `SwSamplerEndToEndTests.test_sw_sampler_source_and_runtime_harness_round_trip_json_diagnostic` in `tests/test_sw_sampler.py` now asserts the round-tripped diagnostic carries exactly the canonical fourteen-name `defaults` set (`bufnum`, `amp`, `grain_size_ms`, `density`, `position`, `position_rate`, `pitch_transpose_semitones`, `pitch_jitter_semitones`, `attack_sec`, `release_sec`, `gate`, `out_bus`, `fx_bus`, `fx_send`) and exactly the canonical eight-stage `signal_chain` set (`grain_trigger`, `pitch_jitter`, `pitch_transpose`, `position_scrub`, `grain_buffer`, `envelope`, `dry_out`, `fx_send_out`) via set equality plus explicit length, lifting the round-tripped coverage from a six-of-fourteen / list-equality spot-check to exhaustive cardinality and content checks. The new assertions are additive — existing assertions and source/runtime behavior are unchanged — so they pass against the current code on first run; full validation (`pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x && ruff check src/ tests/ && mypy src/`) remains clean (`4670 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean), startup identity anchors remain green (`11 passed`), and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
CHANGELOG.md:133:- Added depth-2 sw_sampler end-to-end test coverage (frac-0116): `tests/test_sw_sampler.py` now includes `SwSamplerEndToEndTests`, which drives the existing `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/sw_sampler.scd` granular SynthDef source and the SC-side runtime harness `my-claw/supercollider/test_sw_sampler.scd` through one diagnostic lifecycle. The test extracts every documented SynthDef control default (`bufnum`, `amp`, `grain_size_ms=80.0`, `density=12.0`, `position`, `position_rate`, `pitch_transpose_semitones`, `pitch_jitter_semitones`, `attack_sec`, `release_sec`, `gate>=1`, `out_bus=0`, `fx_bus`, `fx_send=0.4`), verifies the integrated granular signal-chain order (`Impulse.kr` -> `TRand.kr` -> `.midiratio` -> `Sweep.ar`/`Phasor.ar` -> `GrainBuf.ar(... bufnum ...)` -> `EnvGen.kr(Env.asr, gate, doneAction: 2)` -> dry `Out.ar(out_bus, ...)` -> parallel `Out.ar(fx_bus, ...)` send) on a comment-stripped source, confirms the dry write to `out_bus` is not scaled by `fx_send` so the parallel-send architecture is preserved, inspects the SC-side runtime harness for source compile, 2-second render, non-silence, FFT spectral peak, gate=0 release tail, and known-content buffer allocation, and round-trips a JSON-safe diagnostic of the SynthDef name, source path, runtime-harness path, defaults, signal-chain stages, stage positions, and runtime checks through `json.dumps(..., sort_keys=True)`. `tests/test_test_sw_sampler_depth.py` pins the test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the named end-to-end class/method. Existing production behavior remains unchanged because the SCD source and SC-side harness already produced the required one-path output; startup identity anchors remain green (`11 passed`) and the full validation gate (`4669 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remains clean, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
