CHANGELOG.md:247:- Added depth-2 cast-planner end-to-end test coverage (frac-0063): `tests/test_cast_planner.py` now ships a `TestCastPlannerEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public cast-planner surface (`select_cast_ids`, `assemble_cast`, plus the exported `CORE_ROLES` / `SUPPORT_ROLES` / `SAMPLER_METADATA_KEY` constants) through table-driven and looped end-to-end paths. The new tests sweep cast-history/energy combinations to confirm the canonical melody/rhythm/harmony lead with at least one support role across multiple support-role winners; sweep `(voice_count_target, max_chars, expected_size)` cases to verify clamping to `max_chars` and core-role ordering at every size; sweep preferred-synth palettes (`sw_bowed/sw_choir`, `sw_sampler/sw_bell`, `sw_drone/sw_recorder`) to confirm matching characters are promoted into the cast at `voice_count_target=5`; simulate a four-round cast-history rotation that pushes the most-recent support pick out of the next cast; drive multi-piece `assemble_cast` runs to verify piece-derived sampler-selector kwargs (`mode`, `arc_phase`, `mood`, `target_character`) propagate correctly and the sampler summary is mirrored in both the assembled entry's `sample_record` and the metadata mapping; round-trip the assembled diagnostic payload through `json.dumps` with sorted keys; and sweep selector outcomes (`sample`, `None`, `sample`) to verify `sampler_voice` always lands in the cast while `sampler_sample` metadata is attached only when the selector returns a sample. `tests/test_cast_planner_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, real_logic > trivial). Existing `test_select_cast_*`, `test_voice_count_target_*`, `test_preferred_synths_*`, and `test_sampler_*` assertions are preserved unchanged; the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/cast_planner.py` source remains unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4409 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
