docs/coherence-foundations.md:19:Multi-agent systems do not fail because a single agent produces bad output. They fail because agents produce *inconsistent* output --- contradictory decisions, drifted assumptions, violated constraints that no individual agent was tracking. This is the central lesson from both academic research and production deployments.
docs/coherence-foundations.md:93:- **Progressive enforcement (Monitor, Soft, Full).** Production deployments consistently show that starting with full enforcement causes false-positive blocking that erodes developer trust. The solution is progressive rollout: observe first, warn second, block third.
