docs/command-reference.md:359:- The EMSD package now also exists in code, not just in notes: `my-claw/curriculum/` contains a full course catalog and scaffold generator, and the new production-side helpers are `sound_palette_lab.py`, `sample_lab.py`, `mix_engine.py`, `procedural_arc.py`, `dsp_scene_lab.py`, `artistic_identity.py`, and `capstone_engine.py`.
docs/command-reference.md:360:- `emsd_runtime.py` now turns those EMSD helpers into live song context. In tracker solo mode, the composer can derive arc phase, mix targets, sampling intent, DSP blocks, and artistic-identity fields from the current cadence/family/patch/repertoire situation and publish them into `/tmp/composer_state.json`.
docs/command-reference.md:409:- `/tmp/composer_state.json` now also carries EMSD production metadata like `arc_phase`, `mix_target_lufs`, `sample_source`, `sample_transforms`, `dsp_blocks`, `glyph_visual_bias`, and artistic-identity fields, which makes it the authority file for both face text and downstream visual/reactive systems.
